word_group.brief_definition: 一个破败的郊区；一个衰落的郊区
绿树成荫的郊区；庇荫的市郊

bilingual.source: I live in a quiet suburb outside the city.
bilingual.target: 我住在城市外的一个安静的郊区。

bilingual.source: They bought a house in a leafy suburb.
bilingual.target: 他们在一个绿树成荫的郊区买了一栋房子。

bilingual.source: The suburb has many parks and recreational facilities.
bilingual.target: 郊区有很多公园和娱乐设施。

bilingual.source: They live in a wealthy suburb with beautiful houses.
bilingual.target: 他们住在一个有漂亮房子的富有郊区。

bilingual.source: The new shopping mall in the suburb attracts many visitors.
bilingual.target: 新建在郊区的购物中心吸引了很多游客。

bilingual.source: They decided to move to a suburb for a better quality of life.
bilingual.target: 他们决定搬到郊区以获得更好的生活质量。

bilingual.source: Commuting from the suburb to the city center takes about an hour.
bilingual.target: 从郊区通勤到市中心大约需要一个小时。

bilingual.source: They phoned to every ward and suburb.
bilingual.target: 他们给各城区和郊区打电话。

bilingual.source: It is the oldest suburb in Melbourne.
bilingual.target: 这是墨尔本最古老的郊区。

yingyinNormal.en: Another famous seaside suburb not to be missed is Manly. The 30-minute ferry ride from Circular Quay to Manly Wharf is all part of the adventure.
yingyinNormal.zh: 另外，您亦可以不容错过另一个著名的海滨郊区—曼利。从环形码头出发，坐船约 30 分钟就可以到达曼利码头，在这个不可或缺的地方展开历险之旅。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Schneider, a 27-year-old auto technician from the Chicago <highlight>suburbs</highlight>, says he struggled to find a job after graduating from college.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 27岁的施耐德是芝加哥郊区的一名汽车技师。他说，大学毕业后，他很难找到工作。
